docs.text: harmless , silly and fun comedy about dim-witted wrestling fans gordie and sean ( david arquette and scott caan ) who idolize current world championship wrestling heavyweight champion jimmy king ( oliver platt ) .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: when king is screwed out of his title by a corrupt promoter ( joe pantoliano ) , gordie and sean take it upon themselves to find their fallen hero and restore his glory .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: my biggest fear about ready to rumble was dispatched early on , as the filmmakers are quick to show that wresting is indeed choreographed ( but not fake , mind you ) .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the hook of the movie is that gordie and sean are just too stupid to realize that .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: arquette and caan are suitably over the top with their performances , which is exactly what a movie like this requires , and oliver platt ( one of my favorite actors ) is a riot as the drunken washed-up ex-champion .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: many have scoffed at the idea that platt should be playing a heavyweight champion wrestler with an unbeaten record , but for me it just added to the " silly factor " of the film , thereby increasing my enjoyment of it .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: one casting complaint however : rose mcgowan as a sexy dancer ?
docs.label: positive

docs.text: please . . .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: if rose mcgowan is sexy then i'm marilyn manson .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: given the current state of the actual wcw , if oliver platt were appearing as jimmy king right now on wcw programming , he'd be the most popular guy they have .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: on a similar note , the " plot line " of the wresting portions of the film are more entertaining than anything the wcw writers have been able to come up with in the last two years .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: although one does have to ask . . .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: why would any wrestling promoter fire the head wrestler of a company who is both unbeaten and extremely popular with the fans ?
docs.label: positive

docs.text: director brian robbins ( you'll remember him as eric from tv's " head of the class " ) just knows how to make good dumb movies .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: this movie fits in nicely with his previous efforts good burger and varsity blues .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: and screenwriter steven brill ( the epic mighty ducks trilogy , late last night ) manages to keep things both sophomoric and clever at the same time , with almost all the jokes of the film getting a laugh out of me .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the only exceptions to that were : 1 ) a scene involving a van full of singing nuns and 2 ) any scene involving the old woman wrestling fan .
docs.label: positive
